# CrossFit Programming Rule

Use `agents.md` in the repo root as the primary source of truth.

## Non-negotiables

- Keep classes within a hard 60-minute cap.
- Program for single-group start unless explicitly overridden.
- Keep markdown mobile-friendly: short sections, short bullets, no tables.
- Preserve stimulus when scaling, in this order: load, volume, complexity/ROM.
- Include estimates in every conditioning piece:
  - For Time: `Time cap: N min (expected: X-Y min)`
  - AMRAP: `Expected rounds: X-Y (...)`
  - EMOM/intervals: `Target: ...`

## Daily workout structure

For files like `monday.md` to `friday.md`, use this section order when possible:

1. `# Day (DD/MM/YYYY)`
2. `**Setup**` (Equipment, Timing, Stimulus, Scaling A/B, Logistics, Top Cues)
3. `## Warmup (8-12 min)` with R1/R2/R3 RAMP blocks
4. `## Post-Warmup Mobility (60-90s)`
5. `## Strength / Skill` (optional)
6. `## Reset Window` (optional)
7. `## Movement Prep` (before main conditioning)
8. `## Main Conditioning`
9. `## Cooldown` or `## Cooldown & Debrief`

## Warmup and coaching

- Keep warmup implement-light and movement-specific.
- Prefer no barbell in warmup; put barbell rehearsal in Movement Prep.
- Use external, action-oriented coach cues; one cue idea at a time.

## Weekly README and source image workflow

When adding `workouts/2026/week_XX/`:

- Ensure `workouts/2026/week_XX/README.md` has: title, Source Screenshot (if present), Overview, Daily Workouts, Lesson Planning Notes.
- Use relative links (`monday.md`, etc.) in weekly README.
- If source image exists, store as `assets/images/week_XX_source.<ext>`.
- Update root `README.md` under Current Programming with week and screenshot link.

## Canonical references

Prefer and align with:

- `agents.md`
- `guides/CrossFit_Workout_Complete.md`
- `guides/CrossFit_Movement_Warmups.md`
- `guides/Coach_Quickguide.md`
- `guides/Weekly_README_Block_Template.md`
- `research/RAMP_Meta_Annotated.md`
- `research/PAP_PAPE_Research.md`
- `research/Functional_Fitness_Lesson_Planning_Reference.md`

If guidance conflicts, follow `agents.md` and the most recent week format in `workouts/2026/`.
